title: Grateful Dead Live at Hartford Civic Center on 1986-04-04
lineage: Nak DR-2>Tascam CDRW2000>CD >xACT 1.69 (cdparanoia)>WAV>FLAC, all tracks extracted with no errors
description:
Set 1

Jack Straw, Dire Wolf, CC Rider, Candyman, It's All Over Now, Crazy Fingers-> Greatest Story Ever Told-> Day Job

Set 2

Touch Of Grey-> Looks Like Rain-> He's Gone-> Smokestack Lightning-> Drums-> The Wheel-> Stella Blue-> Throwing Stones-> Turn On Your Love Light, E: Box Of Rain

reviews.review_text:
Show some love! First and foremost, this is a quality audience tape from a huge barn in the NE.  The crowd is actually not too nuts to begin with, and the taper does a great job of keeping the music nice and clean.  Not the greatest dynamic range, but nice.
We love ya, Jerry!  Like Muhammad Ali, he got knocked down but never stayed down for the count.  Not his best year, but he never threw in the towel.  He's Gone > Smokestack is the nicest extended playing I could detect, but check out the Stella, too.  He doesn't go for the vocal or guitar crescendo, but lays it out in a soft, always sweet kind of way.  His reach does not exceed his grasp.  Of course, Spring 1986 East Coast tour, five cities and five Box of Rains!!  I saw this one (last night of the tour) and two others, including the very first in Hampton. Bobby is plenty strong, but Jer can really only accompany him, not a great recipe for a great show.  But let's show some love, for the taper and the Band.  I'm going to listen to teh night before 4/3/86 which I remember having a little more gas.  Then I'm going to Hartford Spring Tour 1987 - that gots some juice.

Miss ya Jer and Brent - thankful, too.
